<p>There are many different ways to figure out what information the node table contains.</p>
<ol>
<li>You could use <code>dsm($node);</code> in an appropriate place in your code, assuming you have the <a href="https://drupal.org/project/devel">Devel module</a> installed.</li>
<li>You could also use a poor man's version of dsm, a la <code><a href="https://api.drupal.org/api/drupal/includes!bootstrap.inc/function/drupal_set_message/7">drupal_set_message</a>('&lt;pre&gt;' . print_r($node, 1) . '&lt;/pre&gt;');</code>.</li>
